Felt awful the plane ride and definitely jet lagged. Was good to get out and stretch the legs though.
First time on a map in Hungary. Took it very slow to really see what different parts of the terrain looked like and how it was mapped. Very different from back home.
Long terrain training. Really enjoyed it, most legs were just go straight and keep track of which block of forest you were in.
Middle terrain walk. Very technical.
Running a few controls in the middle terrain. Big take away from this was to know exactly what the control area will look like and have a very definite AP.
Relay terrain training. 5 sets of o-tervals. This terrain was a lot easier than the middle, plus it was fun to have a training where we were pushing speed.
Core workout lead by AdventureGirl!
More training in middle terrain. Felt pretty good, was able to keep track of the vegetation with decent speed. Messed up a couple controls in the circles because I didn't good APs.

Final training on the middle terrain before JWOC. Unfortunately wasn't able to end on a high note as I had a 35 minute control. This started from getting distracted by another runner and then before I found the control it was picked up so I ended finding the same spot a couple times. At least this gave me some relocation practice in the junipers (bailing out the a trail).
First sprint o in a while so it was quite fun, especially with euro street layout that I'm not use to. Overall went pretty well with some route choice mistakes where I missed some diagonals.
Final long terrain training before JWOC. Wasn't very focused so was sloppy pretty much the whole time.
Yoga lead by sensei Naess

First JWOC race!!! Pretty intimidating at the start with the silence. Overall it was a positive first JWOC race - no huge mistake. Although I was quite cautious in the race with staying in contact, even in places where I should have been looking up more where the terrain was open enough that I would have see the control or the feature. As well going through the arena passage destroyed my focus so coming out of it just kinda run into the woods for a bit and then took awhile to relocate.
Morning run with team to loosen up legs after long. Did some strides along the way.

This race didn't go well. Second guessed my self a bunch of times where I would take a couple steps in the direction of route choice before switch my route. As well on 12 made a big missed the ally I should have turned down leading to me having to go all the way around a building. After this I had much less motivation to push myself.
cool down from sprint.

Technical felt quite. The middles were the races I was most worried about after struggling with the terrain the most in training. The terrain for the quali was much more in the forest than I expected. This though meant going in I was more focused on having a clean race and pushing it was second to that but with a easier nav this meant I didn't do as well I a might have I a could have probably pushed harder in through the forest blocks.

Had a rocky start by messing up the first control (very fun), but I think I recovered well and a pretty good rest of the race. Stuck to always taking the simplest route because I figure I would lose as much or more time naviagting though the junipers, with a higher chance of getting lost, than the extra distance to huck it out to a trail.

Was dropped by the pack on the first control both in speed and me messing it up. After this tried to push and just pick off the people in front of me. This was going pretty well until the leg to 9 where I completely lost contact early in the leg then not long after physically and mentally broke to the point where I had trouble focusing enough to figure out what I needed to do to relocate. The controls after 9 also went poorly. It wasn't until the last couple controls where I decided to forget about the overall race and just beat the guy about 20 seconds in front of me. This brought me back online to be about the really focus and push to be about to beat him.

This race went better than the day before, but still with some rather slow legs. As well really messed up the second to last control by several minutes.
Focused on the navigation through this race. This meant I took many legs slower but was happy with my technical execution.

Felt this was on of my better races of oringen. This is because I felt focused pretty much the whole way through and that I was able to have an ok while remaining in control navigationally. Did make one biggish mistake half way through where I messed up my direction and ended up just being slow to get to a trail.

Didn't really get really focused until about half way through after I had a big mistake where I went into a control with no AP and ended up wandering around for a bit. This though reset me focus and after that I felt very committed to the orienteering where before the mistake I wasn't.
